; filter: none; flex: 0 1 auto; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 28px; gap: normal; hyphens: manual; isolation: auto; margin: 0px; marker: none; mask: none; offset: normal; opacity: 1; order: 0; outline: rgb(31, 31, 31) none 0px; overlay: none; padding: 0px; page: auto; perspective: none; position: static; quotes: auto; r: 0px; resize: none; rotate: none; rx: auto; ry: auto; scale: none; speak: normal; stroke: none; transform: none; transition: all 0s ease 0s; translate: none; visibility: visible; x: 0px; y: 0px; zoom: 1;\"> They are used to enhance the shade or correct unwanted nuances when added to the dye.</span></p></div>', 'Mixing ratios: Mix Missea with Oxidant Cream 20 Vol in a 1:1 ratio, or in a 1:2 ratio with 40 Vol when working with lightening products. For a more intense color, mix Missea with Oxidant Cream 20-30-40 Vol in a 1:1 ratio.\r\n\r\nWorking with gray hair:\r\n\r\nIf the amount of gray hair is 0-20%, apply the desired cosmetic color.\r\nIf the amount of gray hair is 20-40%, take 2 parts of the desired cosmetic shade + 1 part of the corresponding natural shade.\r\nIf the amount of gray hair is 40-60%, take 1 part of the desired cosmetic shade + 1 part of the corresponding natural shade.\r\nIf the amount of gray hair is 60-100%, take 1 part of the desired cosmetic shade + 2 parts of the corresponding natural shade (for example: 6.35 + 6.0).\r\nThe recommended mixing ratio is 1:1.\r\n\r\nDevelopment time:\r\n\r\nFor tone-on-tone coloring, apply 3% (10vol) oxidant for 30-40 minutes.\r\nFor coloring gray hair, apply 6% (20vol) oxidant for 30-45 minutes.\r\nTo lighten by 2-3 tones, apply 9% (30vol) oxidant for 30-40 minutes.\r\nTo lighten by 4-5 tones, use intensive lighteners - apply 9% (30vol) or 12% (40vol) oxidant for 40-45 minutes.\r\nAfter coloring: Rinse hair with warm water and shampoo.\r\n\r\nFirst use (uncolored hair):\r\n\r\nDistribute part of the mixture along the entire length of the hair, except for the roots, and wait 20 minutes.\r\nApply the remaining mixture to the hair roots and wait another 20 minutes.\r\nThe total coloring time is 40 minutes.\r\nColoring regrown hair roots:\r\n\r\nApply part of the mixture to the regrown hair roots and wait 20-30 minutes.\r\nDistribute the remaining mixture along the entire length of the hair, except for the roots, and wait another 10-15 minutes.\r\nAdditional information: All AZCOSMETICS GROUP hair dye lines can be mixed with each other to obtain different densities and shades of color.\r\n\r\nAdditionally: Shelf life is 5 years.', NULL, '<p>Product color: 1.0 Black</p><p>Volume: 50 ml</p><p>Number of packages: 1 pc</p><p>Product: hair dye</p><p>Coloring type: permanent</p><p>Texture: cream</p><p>Features: Formaldehyde-free, Natural extracts, Organic cosmetics, With ammonia</p><p>Active ingredient: Vitamin A, Vitamin E, B vitamins, linoleic acid, oil</p><p>Contains ammonia: yes</p><p>Oils and extracts: Argan oil, oil complex, avocado oil, macadamia oil</p><p>Covers gray hair: yes</p>', NULL, NULL, 'missea-hair-dye-black-10-50-ml', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Aqua [Water], Propylene glycol, p-Phenylenediamine, Cetearyl alcohol, (XX), Carbomer, Ammonium hydroxide, 4-Chlororesorcinol, 2-Amino-4-hydroxyethylaminoanisole sulfate, n-Phenyl-p-phenylenediamine sulfate, Sodium sulfite, Ceteareth-25, Parfum [Fragrance], Ascorbic acid, Sodium hydrosulfite, Cocamidopropyl betaine, Tetrasodium EDTA, Laureth-3, Cocamide MEA, Decyl oleate, Polyquaternium-7, Alpha-isomethyl ionone.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p>', '2024-06-10 13:20:54', '2024-06-28 06:34:45'),
