(269, 27, 'Missea Hair Dye Medium Chestnut - 4.00 / 50 ml', 'en', NULL, 'Missea 4.00 Medium Chestnut is the latest development from the AZCOSMETICS GROUP laboratory, a new generation of permanent hair dye. MISSEA provides intense, bright, and luxurious shades thanks to its creamy texture, which allows for easy application to hair, and its perfect formula containing a multitude of conditioning agents and an exclusive complex of oil extracts. Correctors are pure tones that allow you to eliminate unwanted shades or create endless color variations. They are used to enhance the shade or correct unwanted nuances when added to the dye.', '<p>Mixing ratios: Mix Missea with Oxidant Cream 20 Vol in a 1:1 ratio, or in a 1:2 ratio with 40 Vol when working with lightening products. For a more intense color, mix Missea with Oxidant Cream 20-30-40 Vol in a 1:1 ratio. Working with gray hair: If the amount of gray hair is 0-20%, apply the desired cosmetic color. If the amount of gray hair is 20-40%, take 2 parts of the desired cosmetic shade + 1 part of the corresponding natural shade. If the amount of gray hair is 40-60%, take 1 part of the desired cosmetic shade + 1 part of the corresponding natural shade. If the amount of gray hair is 60-100%, take 1 part of the desired cosmetic shade + 2 parts of the corresponding natural shade (for example: 6.35 + 6.0). The recommended mixing ratio is 1:1. Development time: For tone-on-tone coloring, apply 3% (10vol) oxidant for 30-40 minutes. For coloring gray hair, apply 6% (20vol) oxidant for 30-45 minutes. To lighten by 2-3 tones, apply 9% (30vol) oxidant for 30-40 minutes. To lighten by 4-5 tones, use intensive lighteners - apply 9% (30vol) or 12% (40vol) oxidant for 40-45 minutes. After coloring: Rinse hair with warm water and shampoo. First use (uncolored hair): Distribute part of the mixture along the entire length of the hair, except for the roots, and wait 20 minutes. Apply the remaining mixture to the hair roots and wait another 20 minutes. The total coloring time is 40 minutes. Coloring regrown hair roots: Apply part of the mixture to the regrown hair roots and wait 20-30 minutes. Distribute the remaining mixture along the entire length of the hair, except for the roots, and wait another 10-15 minutes. Additional information: All AZCOSMETICS GROUP hair dye lines can be mixed with each other to obtain different densities and shades of color. Additionally: Shelf life is 5 years.<br></p>', NULL, '<p>Product color: 4.00 Medium Chestnut</p><p>Volume: 50 ml</p><p>Number of packages: 1 pc</p><p>Product: hair dye</p><p>Coloring type: permanent</p><p>Texture: cream</p><p>Features: Formaldehyde-free, Natural extracts, Organic cosmetics, With ammonia</p><p>Active ingredient: Vitamin A, Vitamin E, B vitamins, linoleic acid, oil</p><p>Contains ammonia: yes</p><p>Oils and extracts: Argan oil, oil complex, avocado oil, macadamia oil</p><p>Covers gray hair: yes</p>', NULL, NULL, 'missea-hair-dye-medium-chestnut-400-50-ml', '<p>Aqua [Water], Propylene glycol, p-Phenylenediamine, Cetearyl alcohol, (XX), Carbomer, Ammonium hydroxide, 4-Chlororesorcinol, 2-Amino-4-hydroxyethylaminoanisole sulfate, n-Phenyl-p-phenylenediamine sulfate, Sodium sulfite, Ceteareth-25, Parfum [Fragrance], Ascorbic acid, Sodium hydrosulfite, Cocamidopropyl betaine, Tetrasodium EDTA, Laureth-3, Cocamide MEA, Decyl oleate, Polyquaternium-7, Alpha-isomethyl ionone.<br></p>', '2024-06-28 06:41:05', '2024-06-28 06:41:05'),
(270, 28, 'Missea Hair Dye Light Chestnut - 5.00 / 50 ml', 'en', NULL, 'Missea 5.00 Light Chestnut is the latest development from the AZCOSMETICS GROUP laboratory, a new generation of permanent hair dye. MISSEA provides intense, bright, and luxurious shades thanks to its creamy texture, which allows for easy application to hair, and its perfect formula containing a multitude of conditioning agents and an exclusive complex of oil extracts. Correctors are pure tones that allow you to eliminate unwanted shades or create endless color variations. They are used to enhance the shade or correct unwanted nuances when added to the dye.', '<p>Mixing ratios: Mix Missea with Oxidant Cream 20 Vol in a 1:1 ratio, or in a 1:2 ratio with 40 Vol when working with lightening products. For a more intense color, mix Missea with Oxidant Cream 20-30-40 Vol in a 1:1 ratio. Working with gray hair: If the amount of gray hair is 0-20%, apply the desired cosmetic color. If the amount of gray hair is 20-40%, take 2 parts of the desired cosmetic shade + 1 part of the corresponding natural shade. If the amount of gray hair is 40-60%, take 1 part of the desired cosmetic shade + 1 part of the corresponding natural shade. If the amount of gray hair is 60-100%, take 1 part of the desired cosmetic shade + 2 parts of the corresponding natural shade (for example: 6.35 + 6.0). The recommended mixing ratio is 1:1. Development time: For tone-on-tone coloring, apply 3% (10vol) oxidant for 30-40 minutes. For coloring gray hair, apply 6% (20vol) oxidant for 30-45 minutes. To lighten by 2-3 tones, apply 9% (30vol) oxidant for 30-40 minutes. To lighten by 4-5 tones, use intensive lighteners - apply 9% (30vol) or 12% (40vol) oxidant for 40-45 minutes. After coloring: Rinse hair with warm water and shampoo. First use (uncolored hair): Distribute part of the mixture along the entire length of the hair, except for the roots, and wait 20 minutes. Apply the remaining mixture to the hair roots and wait another 20 min